text: Marion Talayrach (born 11 August 1979) is a French rugby union player from Perpignan. She is part of the France women's national rugby union team, competing in the 2005 Women's Six Nations Championship and 2006 Women's Rugby World Cup. She played wing for the USAT XV Toulouges club. == References == Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:French rugby union players Category:Perpignan Category:People from Pyrénées-Orientales Category:Sportspeople from Occitanie
